# Responsive Design Rules

## Mobile-First
Base styles for mobile; enhance at breakpoints:
- `sm: 640px` | `md: 768px` | `lg: 1024px` | `xl: 1280px`

## Layout
```tsx
// Container
<div className="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 md:px-6 lg:px-8" />

// Section spacing
<section className="py-16 md:py-20 lg:py-28" />

// Responsive grid
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6 md:gap-8" />
```

## Navigation
- Hamburger menu below `lg` (1024px)
- Full horizontal nav at `lg` and above

## Touch Targets
- Minimum 44x44px on mobile (48px recommended)
- Prominent phone number and CTA buttons on mobile

## Typography
- Scale down one step on mobile: `text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl`

## Testing
Verify at 320px, 375px, 768px, 1024px, 1440px — no horizontal scroll
